REFERENCE DETAILS
Function signatures (recommended)
- popcount32(n: number) -> number  // treat n as unsigned 32-bit
- popcountBigInt(n: BigInt) -> number  // works for arbitrary precision; returns JS Number (or BigInt if counts may exceed Number)
IMPLEMENTATION NOTES
- In JS, shifting operators on Number coerce to 32-bit integers; for >32-bit work use BigInt and BigInt-aware Kernighan.
- Choose algorithm based on expected input distribution: Kernighan is fast if few bits set; table lookup is consistent and branchless.
